1
00:00:01,101 --> 00:00:03,203
( Birds chirping )

2
00:00:03,237 --> 00:00:04,572
( Knock on door )

3
00:00:04,605 --> 00:00:06,607
Nurse: Rise and shine, sir.

4
00:00:06,640 --> 00:00:09,743
Mr. Kakyoin, are you
feeling any better today?

5
00:00:09,776 --> 00:00:11,544
Kakyoin: To be perfectly honest,

6
00:00:11,578 --> 00:00:14,714
this new way of life
isn’t exactly agreeing with me.

7
00:00:14,748 --> 00:00:16,583
I’m feeling a little on edge.

8
00:00:16,617 --> 00:00:19,120
Nurse: And have you
had any discomfort?

9
00:00:19,152 --> 00:00:20,787
Kakyoin: No,
I haven’t, actually.

10
00:00:20,821 --> 00:00:22,523
The painkillers must be working.

11
00:00:22,556 --> 00:00:24,458
Nurse: Good. Excellent news.

12
00:00:24,491 --> 00:00:26,827
Doctor: We’re thrilled
that you’re feeling better.

13
00:00:26,860 --> 00:00:29,096
Kakyoin: So, doctor,
about these,

14
00:00:29,129 --> 00:00:31,665
how long will I
have to keep them on?

15
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:34,634
The thing is I can’t afford
to wait any longer.

16
00:00:34,668 --> 00:00:36,637
( Doctor clears throat )

17
00:00:36,670 --> 00:00:40,140
Look, kakyoin,
while your eyes will recover,

18
00:00:40,174 --> 00:00:42,677
your condition is
nothing to be taken lightly.

19
00:00:42,709 --> 00:00:44,678
You’ll be in our care
for quite some time,

20
00:00:44,711 --> 00:00:46,213
so please be patient.

21
00:00:46,246 --> 00:00:48,415
The fact of the matter
is we just don’t know

22
00:00:48,448 --> 00:00:50,483
how long you’re
going to remain here.

23
00:00:52,452 --> 00:00:54,587
- Just kidding!
- Kakyoin: Huh?

24
00:00:54,621 --> 00:00:55,822
Doctor: It’s true your body

25
00:00:55,856 --> 00:00:58,292
still needs time
to properly heal itself,

26
00:00:58,325 --> 00:00:59,827
but for some strange reason,

27
00:00:59,860 --> 00:01:02,162
doctors from
the speedwagon foundation

28
00:01:02,196 --> 00:01:04,465
recently contacted us
out of the blue,

29
00:01:04,498 --> 00:01:05,799
and they’ve asked
that we entrust

30
00:01:05,833 --> 00:01:07,335
your medical care to them,

31
00:01:07,367 --> 00:01:08,668
though I have little doubt

32
00:01:08,702 --> 00:01:09,836
their state-of-the-art
medical treatments

33
00:01:09,870 --> 00:01:12,139
will prove to be
more than effective.

34
00:01:12,172 --> 00:01:15,709
But tell me, who are you
behind that schoolboy facade?

35
00:01:15,742 --> 00:01:19,512
Surely you must know
that foundation is world-famous.

36
00:01:19,546 --> 00:01:22,249
I can’t imagine
they’d want anything to do

37
00:01:22,282 --> 00:01:23,750
with an average
high school student.

38
00:01:23,784 --> 00:01:26,253
Kakyoin: Let’s just say
i’m fortunate

39
00:01:26,286 --> 00:01:29,289
to have
a very dependable friend.

40
00:01:29,323 --> 00:01:30,791
( Chuckles )

41
00:01:30,824 --> 00:01:33,460
Thank you for everything,
Mr. Joestar.

42
00:01:33,493 --> 00:01:35,829
I suppose we’ll be
seeing each other again

43
00:01:35,863 --> 00:01:37,765
sooner than we thought.

44
00:01:37,798 --> 00:01:41,935
Jotaro, polnareff, avdol, iggy,

45
00:01:41,969 --> 00:01:43,871
just hang in there.

46
00:01:45,939 --> 00:01:47,941
♪

47
00:01:49,977 --> 00:01:51,979
( Singing in Japanese )

48
00:02:10,731 --> 00:02:12,733
♪

49
00:02:16,703 --> 00:02:18,638
Narrator:
Located in Southern Egypt

50
00:02:18,672 --> 00:02:21,041
is the city of Luxor.

51
00:02:21,074 --> 00:02:23,109
To the ancient Egyptians,
however,

52
00:02:23,143 --> 00:02:25,178
it was the site of thebes,

53
00:02:25,212 --> 00:02:28,816
and it is in this location,
on the west bank of the nile,

54
00:02:28,849 --> 00:02:31,719
that the pharaohs of old
were laid to rest.

55
00:02:31,752 --> 00:02:35,689
It is known
as the valley of the kings.

56
00:02:35,722 --> 00:02:37,123
Avdol: Have you
heard of the tomb

57
00:02:37,157 --> 00:02:38,992
of the great king tutankhamen?

58
00:02:39,026 --> 00:02:41,495
It lies here
in the valley of the kings.

59
00:02:41,528 --> 00:02:44,097
Polnareff: Wow, this place
is chock full of history.

60
00:02:44,131 --> 00:02:46,066
Avdol: If what
i’ve heard is true,

61
00:02:46,099 --> 00:02:48,034
some of the residents
of this area

62
00:02:48,068 --> 00:02:50,437
still dig beneath their houses
in search of treasure

63
00:02:50,470 --> 00:02:52,572
without permission
from the government.

64
00:02:52,606 --> 00:02:54,108
Polnareff:
Think those ancient guys

65
00:02:54,141 --> 00:02:56,176
left behind
any undiscovered treasure?

66
00:02:56,210 --> 00:02:58,179
Avdol: Perhaps they did.

67
00:02:58,212 --> 00:03:01,582
Jotaro: You guys see
where the old man ran off to?

68
00:03:01,615 --> 00:03:03,750
Avdol: Oh, yes. To the bathroom,

69
00:03:03,784 --> 00:03:05,986
and he took iggy,
since he can detect enemies.

70
00:03:06,019 --> 00:03:07,220
Polnareff: Is that so?

71
00:03:07,254 --> 00:03:08,689
Avdol: Do you need to go?

72
00:03:08,722 --> 00:03:10,224
Polnareff: Hmm.

73
00:03:10,257 --> 00:03:13,227
I might, if it’s
a normal bathroom.

74
00:03:14,595 --> 00:03:15,930
- ( Joseph groans )
- ( Iggy groans )

75
00:03:15,963 --> 00:03:19,033
( Joseph groaning )

76
00:03:19,066 --> 00:03:22,136
Oh, my god!

77
00:03:25,772 --> 00:03:28,141
The climate in this place
is so damn arid,

78
00:03:28,175 --> 00:03:31,245
the crap dries up,
turns to dust, and blows away.

79
00:03:31,278 --> 00:03:33,113
Which means
instead of using water,

80
00:03:33,146 --> 00:03:34,948
this toilet
relies solely on wind.

81
00:03:34,982 --> 00:03:37,585
And I don’t see
any toilet paper.

82
00:03:37,618 --> 00:03:39,954
Hmm? Is that...

83
00:03:39,987 --> 00:03:42,056
( Iggy groans )

84
00:03:43,724 --> 00:03:47,228
Joseph: Exactly as I thought.
Some sort of sand basin.

85
00:03:47,261 --> 00:03:49,029
So you wipe your ass...

86
00:03:49,062 --> 00:03:50,564
- With sand?!
- ( Iggy groans )

87
00:03:50,597 --> 00:03:53,033
Narrator: Desert sand
is as sterile as it gets.

88
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:56,102
Joseph: Oh, my god!

89
00:03:56,136 --> 00:03:57,904
( Wails )

90
00:03:58,939 --> 00:04:00,207
I think i’ll pull a polnareff

91
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,242
and wait ’til we
get back to the hotel.

92
00:04:02,276 --> 00:04:05,246
What’s the point of a shack
if you’re going in a hole?

93
00:04:05,279 --> 00:04:08,082
You might as well just do
your business behind a rock.

94
00:04:08,115 --> 00:04:10,818
This thing is weird,
even for a place like Egypt.

95
00:04:10,851 --> 00:04:11,852
Huh?

96
00:04:19,059 --> 00:04:21,962
Eh? Eh? Eh?

97
00:04:21,995 --> 00:04:23,563
- ( Iggy grunts )
- Joseph: Hmm.

98
00:04:23,597 --> 00:04:25,933
This doesn’t make
the slightest bit of sense.

99
00:04:25,966 --> 00:04:27,601
Who in their right mind

100
00:04:27,634 --> 00:04:30,737
would think to put
an electrical outlet in a rock?

101
00:04:30,771 --> 00:04:32,706
I wonder what it’s used for.

102
00:04:32,739 --> 00:04:35,875
There’s no electricity
out here.

103
00:04:35,909 --> 00:04:40,046
( Screams )

104
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:42,716
The damn thing electrocuted me!

105
00:04:42,749 --> 00:04:45,018
Avdol: Mr. Joestar,
is everything all right?

106
00:04:45,052 --> 00:04:46,654
We should probably
get a move on.

107
00:04:46,687 --> 00:04:49,657
( Joseph groans )
Huh? Oh, right.

108
00:04:49,690 --> 00:04:52,560
- ( Sizzling )
- Just give me a second.

109
00:04:52,593 --> 00:04:55,930
( Groans ) That scared
the living daylights out of me.

110
00:04:55,963 --> 00:04:58,299
I can’t believe it’s still live.

111
00:04:58,332 --> 00:05:01,569
I guess the cables must run
underground or something.

112
00:05:01,602 --> 00:05:03,304
You can never tell
with this place.

113
00:05:03,337 --> 00:05:05,739
It’s like traveling
through a fantasyland.

114
00:05:05,772 --> 00:05:07,707
( Outlet humming )

115
00:05:07,741 --> 00:05:09,743
♪

116
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:23,123
Narrator:
Card of the goddess bast.

117
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:25,325
Stand user: Mariah.

118
00:05:30,230 --> 00:05:32,933
Mariah: Now how did
that old saying go again?

119
00:05:32,966 --> 00:05:35,001
Curiosity killed the cat?

120
00:05:35,035 --> 00:05:36,036
( Snaps fingers )

121
00:05:40,374 --> 00:05:42,376
( Static buzzing )

122
00:05:48,749 --> 00:05:51,252
Avdol: We could make it
to Cairo in two days,

123
00:05:51,285 --> 00:05:53,988
but since all of us
are injured and exhausted,

124
00:05:54,021 --> 00:05:56,290
why don’t we spend tonight
and tomorrow in Luxor

125
00:05:56,323 --> 00:05:58,258
and use that time to recuperate?

126
00:05:58,292 --> 00:06:00,194
- ( Hand clicking )
- Joseph: Hmm. Hmm.

127
00:06:00,227 --> 00:06:01,762
Polnareff: Sounds good to me.

128
00:06:01,795 --> 00:06:03,263
Ever since we got to Egypt,

129
00:06:03,297 --> 00:06:06,200
the enemy stands have been
getting stronger and stronger.

130
00:06:06,233 --> 00:06:09,636
We’ve been winning these battles
by the skin of our teeth.

131
00:06:09,670 --> 00:06:10,971
Joseph: Hmm.

132
00:06:11,004 --> 00:06:13,807
Polnareff: Hey, Mr. Joestar,
is something wrong?

133
00:06:13,841 --> 00:06:15,176
Joseph: I’m fine.

134
00:06:15,209 --> 00:06:17,645
My prosthetic hand
is acting funny. That’s all.

135
00:06:17,678 --> 00:06:19,046
It’s nothing to worry about.

136
00:06:19,079 --> 00:06:20,914
I probably just need
to oil the joints.

137
00:06:20,948 --> 00:06:22,716
Polnareff:
Hey, there! Shopkeeper!

138
00:06:22,749 --> 00:06:25,018
Can you please do something
about that radio? It’s busted.

139
00:06:25,052 --> 00:06:26,253
Shopkeeper:
Man, that’s peculiar.

140
00:06:26,286 --> 00:06:27,921
It was made in Japan,

141
00:06:27,955 --> 00:06:29,957
and I just bought
the darn thing. ( Groans )

142
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:31,758
Polnareff: Well,
it’s just static now!

143
00:06:31,792 --> 00:06:33,093
Turn it off!

144
00:06:33,126 --> 00:06:34,260
Joseph: Huh?

145
00:06:34,294 --> 00:06:36,163
Polnareff: Mr. Joestar?

146
00:06:36,196 --> 00:06:38,265
Joseph: Hmm? Yeah, you’re right.

147
00:06:38,298 --> 00:06:40,700
It’d probably be
in our best interest

148
00:06:40,734 --> 00:06:42,970
to rest up
before heading to Cairo.

149
00:06:43,003 --> 00:06:44,371
( Polnareff grunts )

150
00:06:44,404 --> 00:06:47,207
Joseph: Remember,
we can’t let our guard down.

151
00:06:47,241 --> 00:06:49,210
Okay, let’s find a hotel.

152
00:06:49,243 --> 00:06:52,213
( Shopkeeper groans )
What’s going on?

153
00:06:52,246 --> 00:06:53,981
Joseph:
Thanks for the drinks, mister.

154
00:06:54,014 --> 00:06:55,015
Shopkeeper: Uh, come again!

155
00:06:55,048 --> 00:06:57,050
♪

156
00:07:17,437 --> 00:07:18,405
( Music playing )

157
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:19,973
Hey, look at that.

158
00:07:20,007 --> 00:07:21,742
The radio’s working again.

159
00:07:21,775 --> 00:07:23,877
( Man grunts )

160
00:07:30,384 --> 00:07:32,253
- ( Humming )
- What the--

161
00:07:32,286 --> 00:07:34,221
why’s the hammer
suddenly so heavy?

162
00:07:34,254 --> 00:07:36,022
I can’t--huh?

163
00:07:36,056 --> 00:07:38,058
♪

164
00:07:39,059 --> 00:07:40,794
What the hell?

165
00:07:40,827 --> 00:07:43,063
( Wailing )

166
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:49,202
Joseph: Hmm?

167
00:07:49,236 --> 00:07:51,071
Man: Th-the nails!

168
00:07:51,104 --> 00:07:53,206
Ohh! Oh, god, it hurts!

169
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,408
Polnareff: Hey, old man,

170
00:07:54,441 --> 00:07:55,976
did you bang your finger
with the hammer?

171
00:07:56,009 --> 00:07:57,410
You gotta be more careful.

172
00:07:57,444 --> 00:07:59,713
You can’t just go
throwing hammers around.

173
00:07:59,746 --> 00:08:00,814
It’s dangerous.

174
00:08:00,848 --> 00:08:02,950
Jeez.

175
00:08:05,853 --> 00:08:07,755
( Birds chirping )

176
00:08:07,788 --> 00:08:10,824
Avdol: Mr. Joestar,
it’s time to wake up.

177
00:08:10,858 --> 00:08:12,293
Mr. Joestar.

178
00:08:12,326 --> 00:08:14,495
Polnareff: Hey,
hurry it up in there!

179
00:08:14,528 --> 00:08:15,829
( Joseph groans )

180
00:08:15,863 --> 00:08:17,398
Avdol: Polnareff
is going on and on

181
00:08:17,431 --> 00:08:20,200
about the four of us finding
somewhere to eat breakfast.

182
00:08:20,234 --> 00:08:22,069
Polnareff: Hurry,
and wake him up, avdol!

183
00:08:22,102 --> 00:08:24,404
He’s got five minutes
before I come up there!

184
00:08:24,438 --> 00:08:27,241
You know, I thought old people
were supposed to get up early!

185
00:08:29,109 --> 00:08:30,844
Joseph: Damn smart aleck.

186
00:08:30,878 --> 00:08:33,114
He has no respect
for his elders.

187
00:08:33,146 --> 00:08:35,382
Tell him i’ll be down
in just a minute.

188
00:08:35,415 --> 00:08:36,583
Avdol: Right.

189
00:08:37,885 --> 00:08:39,353
Joseph: Well, that’s bizarre.

190
00:08:39,386 --> 00:08:41,221
Why did my watch stop working?

191
00:08:41,255 --> 00:08:43,257
( Avdol laughs )
You know, Mr. Joestar...

192
00:08:43,290 --> 00:08:44,424
Joseph: Hmm?

193
00:08:44,458 --> 00:08:46,327
Avdol: You toss and turn
in your sleep

194
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:48,462
quite a bit for a man your age.

195
00:08:48,495 --> 00:08:51,331
You haven’t noticed yet,
but you’re facing the wrong way.

196
00:08:51,365 --> 00:08:52,800
( Joseph sighs )

197
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:54,368
Avdol: You went to bed
facing south,

198
00:08:54,401 --> 00:08:56,403
but woke up northward
like a compass.

199
00:08:56,436 --> 00:08:58,538
Glad you still have
a youthful spirit.

200
00:08:58,572 --> 00:09:01,175
I’ll be downstairs
when you’re ready.

201
00:09:01,208 --> 00:09:02,209
Joseph: Hmm?

202
00:09:07,581 --> 00:09:10,150
Hmm.

203
00:09:10,184 --> 00:09:11,986
Something strange
has been going on

204
00:09:12,019 --> 00:09:13,387
ever since yesterday afternoon,

205
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:16,123
and for some reason,
my hand is still acting up.

206
00:09:16,156 --> 00:09:18,525
♪

207
00:09:18,559 --> 00:09:19,827
Hmm?

208
00:09:19,860 --> 00:09:21,528
- ( Wheels rolling )
- Huh?

209
00:09:21,562 --> 00:09:23,130
Hmm?

210
00:09:33,607 --> 00:09:34,875
( Yelps )

211
00:09:34,908 --> 00:09:37,110
What is up
with this freaky chair?

212
00:09:37,144 --> 00:09:38,846
The blasted thing’s
moving on its own.

213
00:09:38,879 --> 00:09:39,980
( Grunts )

214
00:09:40,013 --> 00:09:41,948
If I didn’t know any better,

215
00:09:41,982 --> 00:09:44,384
i’d guess the floors
in this place were slanted.

216
00:09:44,418 --> 00:09:46,320
For such a ritzy hotel,

217
00:09:46,353 --> 00:09:49,456
it sure does seem
like it was cheaply made.

218
00:09:51,592 --> 00:09:53,294
Woman: So where
should we go today?

219
00:09:53,327 --> 00:09:55,896
Woman #2: Well, I had an amazing
time looking around karnak,

220
00:09:55,929 --> 00:09:57,197
so i’d say something like that.

221
00:09:57,231 --> 00:09:58,632
Joseph: Mm. ( Chuckles )

222
00:09:58,665 --> 00:10:00,634
Woman #1: How about the valley
of the queens, instead?

223
00:10:00,667 --> 00:10:02,869
- ( Metal humming )
- ( Shrieks )

224
00:10:02,903 --> 00:10:05,339
What the hell do you think
you’re doing, you old pervert?!

225
00:10:05,372 --> 00:10:07,474
- Joseph: Huh?
- Woman #1: Jackass!

226
00:10:07,508 --> 00:10:11,278
Joseph: I don’t understand.
What the hell just happened?

227
00:10:11,311 --> 00:10:13,313
♪

228
00:10:17,117 --> 00:10:19,286
( Humming )

229
00:10:19,319 --> 00:10:21,454
Woman #3: Ooh!

230
00:10:22,589 --> 00:10:24,424
( Coos )

231
00:10:24,458 --> 00:10:25,893
( Joseph groans )

232
00:10:25,926 --> 00:10:28,028
Woman #3: I do appreciate
your forwardness,

233
00:10:28,061 --> 00:10:29,629
but you need
to work on your approach,

234
00:10:29,663 --> 00:10:32,266
you naughty, naughty man.
( Giggles )

235
00:10:32,299 --> 00:10:37,271
But that said,
you’re just my t-y-p-e.

236
00:10:37,304 --> 00:10:38,272
Mwah.

237
00:10:38,305 --> 00:10:41,175
Joseph: Oh, my god!

238
00:10:41,208 --> 00:10:42,576
( Gasping )

239
00:10:42,609 --> 00:10:44,010
I was right!

240
00:10:44,044 --> 00:10:45,646
Something’s wrong here,
really wrong,

241
00:10:45,679 --> 00:10:48,382
and it’s been this way
ever since yesterday afternoon!

242
00:10:49,449 --> 00:10:51,051
Ahh!

243
00:10:51,084 --> 00:10:52,953
Wait. What the--

244
00:10:52,986 --> 00:10:55,255
th-they’re stuck to my hand!

245
00:10:55,289 --> 00:10:57,992
Hang on.
It’s all starting to make sense,

246
00:10:58,025 --> 00:11:00,194
the reason
why all these metal objects

247
00:11:00,227 --> 00:11:02,162
are suddenly attracted to me.

248
00:11:02,196 --> 00:11:05,166
But it can’t be.
That’s impossible.

249
00:11:05,199 --> 00:11:06,967
( Humming )

250
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,568
Yaah!

251
00:11:08,602 --> 00:11:10,337
It looks like I was right!

252
00:11:10,370 --> 00:11:13,406
My body’s turned into a magnet!

253
00:11:15,475 --> 00:11:16,543
( Screams )

